                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 30, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that a constitutional government will be proclaimed to-night;
                    full parliamentary government, the Emperor reserving <pb facs="0897" n="777"
                        xml:id="pg_777"/> the right of veto; freedom of the press and person and of
                    speech, habeas corpus, and inviolability of domicile. The parliament appoints
                    the ministers. The franchise is extended to all classes. Count Witte, prime
                    minister.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
